issue.description:
The where rule reads: NotActual: NOT ('Activity_actual' in TYPEOF(predicted));
In fact TYPEOF returns UPPERCASE complete names (i.e. with the schema prepended). Hence this has to read: WR1: NOT ('ACTIVITY_AS_REALIZED.ACTIVITY_ACTUAL' in TYPEOF(predicted));
It is also the STEP convention to use WR1 (for where rule 1) rather than meaningful names for rule labels.

schema name in wr not being replaced because it is not spelled correctly (missing '_arm'). (* ------------------------------------------------------------ D:\abf\stepmod\ballots\ballots\ap233wd2\express\arm\activity_as_realized_arm.exp ------------------------------------------------------------ *)
(* $Id: arm.exp,v 1.8 2004/12/08 08:28:29 robbod Exp $ ISO TC184/SC4/WG12 N2992 - ISO/TS 10303-1259 Activity as realized - EXPRESS ARM Supersedes ISO TC184/SC4/WG12 N2369 *)
SCHEMA Activity_as_realized_arm;
USE FROM Activity_arm; -- ISO/TS 10303-1047
ENTITY Activity_actual SUBTYPE OF (Activity); END_ENTITY;
ENTITY Activity_happening SUBTYPE OF (Activity_relationship); SELF\Activity_relationship.relating_activity RENAMED actual : Activity_actual; SELF\Activity_relationship.related_activity RENAMED predicted : Activity; WHERE WR1: NOT ('ACTIVITY_AS_REALIZED.ACTIVITY_ACTUAL' IN TYPEOF(predicted)); >>> ^_ARM END_ENTITY;
END_SCHEMA; -- Activity_as_realized_arm
